description._content: Image Description from historic lecture booklet: "In central and western Australia there are many tribes of native people who live in most primitive ways. Their relationship to the native peoples of New Zealand, of the islands of the Pacific, of Asia, and of Africa is not known, but they are usually classes with the black race."
